### What version of Bun is running?

1.1.20+ae1948925

### What platform is your computer?

Microsoft Windows NT 10.0.22631.0 x64

### What steps can reproduce the bug?

1. Make an empty project (`bun init`)
2. Install `tar` (`bun add tar`)
3. Download a `.tar.gz` (mine is <https://api.github.com/repos/steinjs/stein/tarball/main>) as `main.tar.gz`
4. Write the following in `index.ts` : 
```typescript
import { extract } from "tar";
import { mkdirSync, rmSync } from "node:fs"

rmSync("./extracted", { recursive: true, force: true });
mkdirSync("./extracted");

const template = { subdir: "/examples/bare" }
const subdir = template.subdir?.replace(/^\//, "") || "";

await extract({
  file: "./main.tar.gz",
  cwd: "./extracted",
  onentry(entry) {
    entry.path = entry.path.split("/").splice(1).join("/");

    if (subdir) {
      if (entry.path.startsWith(subdir + "/")) {
        // Rewrite path
        entry.path = entry.path.slice(subdir.length);
      } else {
        // Skip
        entry.path = "";
      }
    }
  },
});
```

> Note that this is the *actual* (but simpler here) code used by the [`unjs/giget`](https://github.com/unjs/giget) library : <https://github.com/unjs/giget/blob/a2acbcc422975be9a9c338a96cc9d894a5053711/src/giget.ts#L143-L160>

### What is the expected behavior?

Only the content of `/examples/bare` should be extracted in the `./extracted` directory.

The following happens correctly in Node.js : 

![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ed3dcb44-09ae-4042-8782-e60910a7dcd6)


### What do you see instead?

Only the directories are created but no files.

![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4a151c1b-8c6b-4897-a94d-1f741732a443)

(empty folder and empty `src`)

![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/449b6568-d575-45c8-b065-2bef24ca029d)


### Additional information

Note that the previous code works on Linux and macOS without any issue, so it's probably a Windows-only issue.

EDIT: just tried without the `onentry` option and only the directories gets extracted but no file.

